N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 3 ยง 416.3 - Branching applications

State Regulations

All applications submitted for the prior approval of the
superintendent to establish a branch or branches by any licensed check casher
shall be accompanied by information demonstrating that the applicant has or
will have an anti-money laundering program that satisfies the requirements set
forth in section
416.1
of this

Part. Notes
